Task Manager project in Angular
Steps followed in the Task manager project for running and adding dependencies

1: Initialized the app with    	
>ng new TaskManager --style=scss --routing

1.1 : After loading the application open it using
 >ng serve --open //Automatically opens page in browser
 >ng serve --open port=1024-65000 //To specify other ports as anugular opens in port 4200 as default port

 1.2 : Flow of Execution 
 >index.html --> main.ts -->app.module.ts --> app.component.ts + app.component.html

 1.3 : Adding Bootstrap to Angular
 > npm install jquery --save
 > npm install popper.js --save
 > npm install bootstrap --save